args:
The prince's party arrives in Grams and is
amazed by the grandeur of the cityscape—but
they also see a great disparity between citizens.
When the city guard oppresses a man of low
rank, Ranzal takes matters into his own hands,
forcing the party to support him in combat.
Once we crest this hill, we should be able\nto see the city.
Eee hee hee! My informants never fail.\nNow behold the Holy City of Grams\nin all of her splendor!
It even puts Sol Alberia to shame.
Not just the size, but the sheer beauty.\nThe entire city glitters like a rare jewel.
And the man named Gatov is\nsomewhere inside.
I must give you all a final warning before\nwe make our initial foray into the city.
Grams and Alberia are still in conflict.
If it becomes known that we are a party of\nAlberian royals, we will, in all likelihood,\nface considerable danger.
Then we shall keep our guards high.
Make every effort not to do anything too\nterribly conspicuous in town. I trust there\nwon't be any problem with that?
We've got it, Chelle.\nBest behavior, everybody!
And a pleasant afternoon to you.
We seem to have reached the city center.
I'd heard stories, but had no idea it\nwas THIS magnificent.

The waterways captivate with elegance,
and the houses are more like palaces.
It's hard to believe private citizens live
in such fine abodes.
And the attire and conduct of people\nwe pass in the street are equally fine.
Okay, what's that massive building way\noff there in the distance?
That is the August Cathedral—a symbol\nof the city's faith, and of the massive\ninfluence of the Ilian Church of Grams.
It's even bigger than the royal castle of\nAlberia. By a significant margin, at that.
Is there any kind of monarch here, Chelle?
Indeed there is. But nowadays, the royal\nfamily are no more than puppets.
As you will gather from the majesty of the\ncathedral, what truly governs this city is\nthe Ilian Church of Grams.
The church engages in open politicking?\nSuch actions are almost unthinkable\nfrom an Alberian perspective.
I knew the they differed in their\ninterpretation of Church doctrine,\nbut I didn't realize the extent.
Well, since we're here, how's about we\ngo check out the cathedral up close?
You damn persistent old man!\nGet the hell out of here!
Please, I beg of you! I must worship at\nthe August Cathedral, whatever it takes!

How many times do I have to tell you this?
Entrance into the Cathedral District is
forbidden for someone with your lowly
place in the Canon!
Yet if I can but pray there for a moment,\nI know my daughter's illness will be cured!

It doesn't matter what your circumstances
are. It would serve you better to do good
and fill your purse with virtue rather than
try to overstep your station.

Good deeds bring you closer to the
teachings of the Goddess Ilia, thereby
raising your station in the Canon. Only
then can you worship at the cathedral.
But my daughter's condition is dire!\nPlease, just this once! I beg you again!
Ignorant lout! Get out of my sight!
I can't stand here and abide such cruelty!\nBut if I cause a scene...
You do well to exercise restraint, Brother.\nWe must not interfere.
Believe me, I understand how you feel.\nBut we cannot engage in any behavior\nthat would attract the eyes of the public.
I can't just stand here and watch, though.
Sorry, Chelle, but I ain't much for all\nthis sittin' on our hands crap.
Ya seriously ain't gonna let that old timer\ndo his prayin' in the cathedral?
I am not. Church doctrine is absolute,\nand not to be twisted about for the mere\nwhims of some sad old man.
A doctrine what tells ya to kick old men\nout into the street ain't worth crap.
I ain't doin' nothing of the sort—though I\nAM pretty sure Ilia don't look kindly on her\nfollowers roughin' people up.
Heathen! Infidel! All guards, to me!\nCrush this whelp where he stands!
Great, now Ranzal's gone and got himself\nsurrounded. What do we do?
We have to help him, Chelle.
For heaven's sake, we've barely been in\ntown for an HOUR! I swear, you people...
But what's done is done, I suppose. Let's\ntake them out quickly and be done with it!
